<div class="row">
	<div class="small-12 medium-8 columns">
		<h1>East London Venues</h1>
		
		<hr> 
		
		<div class="review">
			<a href="http://www.forgeandco.co.uk/" target="_blank">
			<h2>Forge & Co, Shoreditch</h2>
			</a>
			<p>(154-158 Shoreditch High St, E1 6HU)</p>
			<p>Defines itself ‘unique social workspace’ this is a renovated old building. There are 5 floors, including an art gallery which is great for creative meetings and potential clients. They also have fresh healthy juices as well as coffee.</p>
			<div class="score">
				<p>
				Wi-Fi: 4/5<br>
				Service: 2/5<br>
				Atmosphere: 4/5<br>
				Power Points: 4/5</br>
				Coffee/Menu: 3/5<br>
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		
		<hr> 
		
		<div class="review">
			<h2>Love Shake, Dalston</h2>
			<p>(5 Kingsland Road E2 8 AA)</p>
			<p>It's close to the station and good for freelancers. Better for milkshakes than coffee, great reasonably priced menu. Best to go early and enjoy the lighting, can become quite dark & loud. Ideal for short stay. Try the peanut butter & Oreo milkshake.</p>
			<div class="score">
				<p>
				Wi-Fi: 2/5<br>
				Service: 2/5<br>
				Atmosphere: 1/5<br>
				Power Points: 1/5</br>
				Coffee/Menu: 1/5<br>
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<hr> 
		
		<div class="review">
		  <a href="http://hoi-polloi.co.uk/" target="_blank">
			<h2>Hoi Polloi, Shoreditch</h2>
			</a>
			<p>(100 Shoreditch High Street, London, E1 6JQ)</p>
			<p>A cool professional space with a various range of healthy juices to keep you feeling refreshed. Hoi Polloi has power sockets at every table, so ideal for focus groups and meetings.</p>
			<div class="score">
				<p>
				Wi-Fi: 4/5<br>
				Service: 3/5<br>
				Atmosphere: 3/5<br>
				Power Points: 5/5</br>
				Coffee/Menu: 4/5<br>
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>


		<hr> 
		
		<div class="review">
			<a href="http://thelaundrye8.com/" target="_blank">
			<h2>The Laundry, London fields</h2>
			</a>
			<p>(2-18 Warburton Road, London, E8 3FN)</p>
			<p>Interestingly owned by the guitarist of Radiohead. Ideal for combining drinks with work, or taking a potential client. The spacious décor makes it naturally light and perfect for those who enjoy listening to music as they work. The setting is brilliant for networking and is close to the station.</p>
			<div class="score">
				<p>
				Wi-Fi: 3/5<br>
				Service: 3/5<br>
				Atmosphere: 5/5<br>
				Power Points: ?/5</br>
				Coffee/Menu: 4/5<br>
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<hr> 
		
		<div class="review">
			<a href="https://www.shoreditchhouse.com/" target="_blank">
			<h2>Shoreditch House, Shoreditch</h2>
			</a>
			<p>(Ebor Street, Shoreditch, London, E1 6AW)</p>
			<p>Ultra-exclusive and perfect for networking. This is ideal for freelancers who want the opportunity to work along elite London. There is a monthly membership and an upscale menu. It’s known as a celebrity hotspot.</p>
			<div class="score">
				<p>
				Wi-Fi: 3/5<br>
				Service: 3/5<br>
				Atmosphere: 5/5<br>
				Power Points: 3/5</br>
				Coffee/Menu: 3/5<br>
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<hr> 
		
		<div class="review">
			<a href="www.lookmumnohands.com/" target="_blank">
			<h2>Look Mum No Hands, Old street </h2>
			</a>
			<p>(49 Old Street, London, EC1V 9HX)
</p>
			<p>This one is great if you’re an avid cyclist, defines itself as a ‘café/workshop’ so it’s easy and comfortable to spend hours on end there. There is a eco-hipster persona to the establishment, and a range of places to plug yourself in. Wi-Fi goes down during lunch hour to free up space for eating.</p>
			<div class="score">
				<p>
				Wi-Fi: 3/5<br>
				Service: 3/5<br>
				Atmosphere: 5/5<br>
				Power Points: 3/5</br>
				Coffee/Menu: 5/5<br>
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<hr> 
		
		<div class="review">
		  <a href="https://thehoxton.com/" target="_blank">
			<h2>Hoxton Hotel, Old street</h2>
			</a>
			<p>(81 Great Eastern St, London EC2A 3HU)</p>
			<p>This is less busy during weekdays, and a spacious and cozy environment. The Menu is a tad expensive considering it’s simplicity, but the atmosphere is great and its perfect for working in all day, then drinking in the evening. If you want to be left alone submerge into your headphones without distraction it’s perfect.</p>
			<div class="score">
				<p>
				Wi-Fi: 3/5<br>
				Service: 2/5<br>
				Atmosphere: 2/5<br>
				Power Points: ?/5</br>
				Coffee/Menu: 3/5<br>
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		
		<hr> 
		
		<div class="review">
			<a href="https://www.campus.co/london/en" target="_blank">
			<h2>Google Campus, Old Street</h2>
			</a>
			<p>(4-5 Bonhill Street, London EC2A 4BX)</p>
			<p>This is ideal for groups. It's full of likeminded people working away. The feeling is busy but focussed, so it's perfect for working alone or in a focus group.</p>
			<div class="score">
				<p>
				Wi-Fi: 3/5<br>
				Service: 2/5<br>
				Atmosphere: 2/5<br>
				Power Points: 5/5</br>
				Coffee/Menu: 2/5<br>
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

<hr> 
		
		<div class="review">
			<a href="http://www.wearetbc.com/" target="_blank">
			<h2>The Book Club, Shoreditch</h2>
			</a>
			<p>(100-106 Leonard St, London EC2A 4RH)</p>
			<p>This is perfect for early morning meetings; they have Life drawing classes and Informative talks that take place so check out what they have planned. It’s open, bright and during weekdays doesn’t get overbearingly busy. </p>
			<div class="score">
				<p>
				Wi-Fi: 2/5<br>
				Service: 2/5<br>
				Atmosphere: 2/5<br>
				Power Points: 5/5</br>
				Coffee/Menu: 2/5<br>
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

<hr> 
		
		<div class="review">
			<a href="http://foxcroftandginger.co.uk/" target="_blank">
			<h2>Foxcroft & Ginger</h2>
			</a>
			<p>(68-89 Mile End Rd, Whitechapel, Greater London, E1 4TT)</p>
			<p>This has a trendy setting, with an industrial feel to it. The staff are friendly and encourage people to do work inside. The coffee is great and the Breakfast menu is popular. This is ideal students or workers, there is a D-I-Y element to the décor that makes it informal and comfortable.</p>
			<div class="score">
				<p>
				Wi-Fi: 4/5<br>
				Service: 2/5<br>
				Atmosphere: 2/5<br>
				Power Points: 1/5</br>
				Coffee/Menu: 4/5<br>
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

